@@ -0,0 +1,55 @@
+---
+title: hive setup
+type: command
+source: lib/hive/commands/setup.rb, lib/hive/commands/setup/backend_prompt.rb, lib/hive/local/dependency_check.rb, lib/hive/local/daemon_consistency.rb
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [command, setup, local, install, daemon, web]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: `hive setup` is the one-command local (non-Docker) setup path
+that provisions and validates the Hive CLI, Rails web bundle, qmd, daemon
+service, project enrollment, and web launch. Local mode operates on the
+user's real Hive/XDG state and checked-out repos (no sandbox); the web UI
+binds `127.0.0.1:4567`. See [[local-mode]].
+
+## Flags
+
+- (none) — full setup: diagnostics + ensure daemon + enroll project +
+  persist global agent backends + print web launch path.
+- `--check` — non-mutating: run the dependency + daemon-consistency
+  diagnostics only; exit 65 if any check fails, emitting the exact fix
+  command for each failure.
+- `--start-web` — additionally `hive web install && hive web start`.
+- `--json` — machine-readable report of the diagnostic results and the
+  actions taken (dependencies[], daemon{}, ok).
+
+## What it does
+
+1. **Diagnostics** (`Hive::Local::DependencyCheck` +
+   `Hive::Local::DaemonConsistency`): verifies Ruby 3.4, git, tmux, gh
+   (present AND authenticated), claude (version >= `Hive::MIN_CLAUDE_VERSION`),
+   codex, node, npm, qmd, the Rails web bundle (`bundle check`, never
+   auto-installs), sqlite storage writability; and checks the installed
+   daemon unit's binary vs the current CLI binary. Never silently installs
+   or authenticates external agent CLIs — diagnoses and emits the exact
+   command the operator must run.
+2. **Daemon**: if the unit is drifted, surfaces the repair command
+   (`hive daemon install --force`) without clobbering a hand-edited unit;
+   otherwise runs `hive daemon install`. Starts the daemon (`hive daemon
+   start --detach`) if not already running.
+3. **Project enrollment**: if the cwd is a registered project, runs
+   `hive daemon enable <project>`; otherwise prints guidance to run
+   `hive init`.
+4. **Agent backends**: interactive `BackendPrompt` (defaults when
+   non-interactive / EOF) persisted via `Hive::Config.write_global_agents!`.
+5. **Web**: prints the foreground `hive web` command and the managed-service
+   alternative; with `--start-web`, installs and starts the web service.
+
+## Exit codes
+
+- 0 success (or `--check` all-pass).
+- 65 a `--check` diagnostic failed.
+
+Backlinks: [[local-mode]], [[commands/web]], [[commands/daemon]],
+[[commands/init]].
diff --git a/wiki/gaps.md b/wiki/gaps.md
index 2d71cc61..5737bffc 100644
--- a/wiki/gaps.md
+++ b/wiki/gaps.md
@@ -317,3 +317,33 @@ genuine clean verdict could fail to match and `:error`/retry (worst case
 emit the strict `## High/Medium/Nit` + `No findings.` format so the prose path
 is never exercised; until then, watch `reviews/errors-NN.md` tails for
 clean-but-rejected verdicts and extend `CLEAN_VERDICT` as new phrasings appear.
+
+## local-mode: loopback auth + non-loopback refusal (2026-07-10)
+
+The local (non-Docker) web install/run mode ([[local-mode]]) added
+`hive setup`, `hive web install/start/stop/status/restart`, dependency
+diagnostics, and daemon binary-consistency checking. Two auth-related
+acceptance points from the plan are intentionally deferred:
+
+- **No auth on loopback by default**: the Rails app's GitHub owner-gate
+  auth model is unchanged. Making loopback auth-free is a web-app change
+  that risks the existing hivebox owner-gate tests and was out of scope
+  for the first slice. Today loopback still goes through the owner flow.
+- **Refuse non-loopback without auth/owner or an unsafe flag**: `hive web`
+  still only WARNS on a `0.0.0.0` bind without an https origin, because a
+  hard refusal would break the claimable (ownerless) Docker hivebox at
+  first boot, where `web.github.owner` is nil and the origin is http.
+  Implementing the refusal requires distinguishing the Docker/hivebox
+  context from local mode (e.g. an env marker) before it is safe.
+
+## local-mode: daemon version drift not detectable from the unit file (2026-07-10)
+
+`Hive::Local::DaemonConsistency` compares the installed daemon unit's
+binary PATH to the current CLI binary (catching the documented
+`/usr/bin/hive` drift) but cannot detect version drift where the same
+path was upgraded but the running daemon was not restarted. The daemon
+does not currently expose its `Hive::VERSION` over IPC. Version drift is
+partially addressed by `hive setup` running `hive daemon install` (which
+restarts on upgrade), but a true running-version probe (e.g. the daemon
+writing its version to a state file, or `/proc/<pid>/environ` HIVE_BIN)
+is a future enhancement.
