diff --git a/wiki/local-mode.md b/wiki/local-mode.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..d0795a7a
--- /dev/null
+++ b/wiki/local-mode.md
@@ -0,0 +1,72 @@
+---
+title: local-mode
+type: module
+source: lib/hive/local/, lib/hive/commands/setup.rb, lib/hive/commands/web.rb, lib/hive/commands/web/service_installer.rb, lib/hive/commands/web/service_control.rb, examples/systemd/hive-web.service, examples/launchd/hive-web.plist
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [local, web, daemon, setup, install, openclaw]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: Local (non-Docker) install/run mode lets an operator run the Hive
+web UI and daemon on their own Linux/macOS machine, operating on the user's
+real Hive/XDG state and checked-out repos (no sandbox), with the daemon
+picking up new tasks by default. It mirrors the OpenClaw local UX pattern:
+zero/low-config loopback server, clear lifecycle commands, health checks,
+port handling, diagnostics. Docker/hivebox remains an alternative
+install/run path, not replaced.
+
+## Commands
+
+- `hive setup` — one-command local setup (see [[commands/setup]]).
+- `hive web [SUBCOMMAND]` — `run` (foreground, always works) or managed
+  service lifecycle `install`/`start`/`stop`/`restart`/`status` (see
+  [[commands/web]]).
+- The daemon lifecycle is unchanged (`hive daemon install/start/status`);
+  `hive setup` ensures the daemon service is installed and running with
+  the same Hive binary as the CLI.
+
+## Networking / auth
+
+- Default bind `127.0.0.1:4567` (loopback), unchanged from the existing
+  `web:` config defaults.
+- The Rails app's GitHub owner-gate auth model is **unchanged** in this
+  slice — "no auth on loopback by default" is a future web-app change
+  (see [[gaps]]). The hivebox claim/owner flow stays Docker-oriented.
+- Non-loopback bind (`0.0.0.0`) without an https origin still only WARNS
+  rather than refusing, preserving the hivebox trusted-proxy posture and
+  the claimable first-boot box. Refusing non-loopback without auth/owner
+  or an unsafe flag is deferred (it would break the claimable Docker box).
+
+## State / data model
+
+- Local mode operates directly on the user's real `Hive::Paths.state_home`
+  (XDG), existing `hive` config, and actual checked-out repos. TUI and web
+  share one source of truth. No separate sandbox dir (Docker keeps `/data`).
+- The Rails web app is NOT packaged in the gem — local web mode requires
+  the app to exist (a source checkout, `HIVEBOX_WEB_APP_DIR`, or a layout
+  that bundles it). `Hive::Local::DependencyCheck` verifies the web bundle.
+
+## Diagnostics
+
+- `Hive::Local::DependencyCheck` — non-Docker prerequisite verifier
+  (Ruby 3.4, git, tmux, gh+auth, claude version-gated, codex, node, npm,
+  qmd, web bundle, sqlite storage). Never silently installs/authenticates
+  external agent CLIs; emits exact fix commands. Injectable collaborators
+  for unit testing.
+- `Hive::Local::DaemonConsistency` — non-mutating check that the installed
+  daemon unit's binary matches the current CLI binary (the documented
+  `/usr/bin/hive` drift). Reports `:consistent`/`:drifted`/`:not_installed`/
+  `:unsupported` with a repair command. Resolves through realpath so a
+  symlinked wrapper compares equal. Version drift (same path, upgraded
+  binary not restarted) is not detectable from the unit file alone — see
+  [[gaps]].
+
+## Schemas
+
+- `hive-web-install.v1.json` registered (mirrors `hive-daemon-install` /
+  `hive-bot-install`) so agents can branch `hive web install --json`
+  outcomes. `hive web status` / lifecycle emit sans-schema envelopes (like
+  `hive tui --json`'s rejection) since they are operator-facing.
+
+Backlinks: [[commands/web]], [[commands/setup]], [[commands/daemon]],
+[[architecture]], [[gaps]].
