+---
+timestamp: 2026-07-10T08:00:00Z
+title: First-class local (non-Docker) Hive web install/run mode
+---
+
+- Added a first-class **local (non-Docker) install/run mode** for the Hive
+  web UI, alongside the existing Docker/hivebox path (Docker remains
+  supported, not replaced). See [[local-mode]] and [[commands/setup]].
+- `hive web` now accepts a SUBCOMMAND: `run` (foreground, the existing
+  behavior, always works), `install`/`start`/`stop`/`restart`/`status`
+  for the optional managed web service (systemd-user on Linux, launchd on
+  macOS), mirroring `hive daemon install` via
+  `Hive::Commands::Web::ServiceInstaller` and `ServiceControl`. New unit
+  templates: `examples/systemd/hive-web.service`, `examples/launchd/hive-web.plist`.
+  Registered the `hive-web-install` schema (mirrors `hive-daemon-install`).
+- `hive setup` (new) provisions/validates local mode: runs dependency
+  diagnostics, ensures the daemon service is installed and running with
+  the same Hive binary as the CLI, enrolls the current project, persists
+  global agent backends, and prints the web launch path.
+  `--check` is non-mutating; `--start-web` installs+starts the web service.
+- `Hive::Local::DependencyCheck` verifies Ruby 3.4, git, tmux, gh
+  (present AND authenticated), claude (version-gated), codex, node, npm,
+  qmd, the Rails web bundle (bundle check), sqlite storage. NEVER silently
+  installs/authenticates external agent CLIs — diagnoses + emits fix commands.
+- `Hive::Local::DaemonConsistency` non-mutatingly checks the installed
+  daemon unit's binary vs the current CLI binary (the documented
+  `/usr/bin/hive` drift); reports repair command `hive daemon install --force`.
+- Local mode operates on the user's real Hive/XDG state and checked-out
+  repos (no sandbox). Default bind remains `127.0.0.1:4567` (loopback).
+- Open gap (see [[gaps]]): the Rails app's GitHub owner-gate auth model is
+  unchanged — "no auth on loopback by default" is a future web-app change,
+  not in this slice. Non-loopback bind still only warns (the hivebox
+  trusted-proxy posture) rather than refusing, to avoid breaking the
+  claimable Docker box.
